<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9803> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9803" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cichorius identifies him as a Tribune of the Soldiers based on the list of members of the staff of Pompeius Strabo at Asculum (ILS 8888; RS 144-155)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8731> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8731" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 750, footnote 345" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7483> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7483" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. 81, procos. in Cilicia 80-79. See MRR 2.76, 80, 84. On his return he was prosecuted by M. Aemilius Scaurus, the younger, and condemned. See Badian, PBSR 33, 1965, 48-51, with his probable filiation. See also Cic. Scaur. 45-46; Ascon. 16C, 74C.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7175> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7175" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 72. Sumner presents a good case for identifying the Cn. Cornelius Cn. f. Pal. in Pompeius Strabo's consilium at Asculum with the consul of 72 (Orators 124-126; Shackleton Bailey, Studies 112-113). The filiation given above assumes that he was an adoptive son of Cn. Cornelius Lentulus (178). Cos. 97. See Sumner and Shackleton Bailey, above, and also Criniti, L'Epigrafe di Asculum 108-110; who favors Cn. Cornelius Dolabella (135), Pr. urb. 81. Monetalis: Cn. (Cornelius) (Cn. f.) Lentul(us) (Clodianus). Add in MRR 2.437, and refer to Crawford, RRC 1.356-357, no. 345, 88? B.C.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4269> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4269" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Cilicia. See 80, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4242> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4242" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul (Ps.-Ascon. 208 Stangl; Schol. Gron. 325 Stangl) in Cilicia (Cic. Verr. 1.11; 2.1.41-102 passim; 2.2.109; 2.3.177; Ascon. 26, and 74C; Ps.-Ascon. 194, 206, 208, 234, 236, 240, 242, 245 Stangl; Schol. Gron. 325, 329, 333 Stangl; of. Iuv. Sat. 8. 105; see Legates, on Verres; and above, Quaestors, on Malleolus). See 79, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4199> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4199" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Quinct. 30; Corn. in Ascon. 74C; see 80, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3923> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3923" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "11 The cognomen might also be Blasio or Lentulus. Cichorius favors Dolabella beeause the later careers of the known Dolabellas parallel so closely that of Lepidus." .
